class dataset:
    def __init__(self):
        self.size_o = 10
        self.size_i = 32 * 32 * 3
        self.load_labels()
        self.loadbatch = {}
        self.encode_label = preprocessing.LabelBinarizer()
        self.encode_label.fit([x for x in range(self.size_o)])

    def load_labels(self):
        with open('cifar-10-batches-py/batches.meta', 'rb') as f:
            data = pickle.load(f, encoding='bytes')
            self.labels = [x.decode('ascii') for x in data[b'label_names']]

    def getbat(self, batch_name):
        if not batch_name in self.loadbatch:
            with open('cifar-10-batches-py/' + batch_name, 'rb') as f:
                data = pickle.load(f, encoding='bytes')
                
            data[b'labels'] = np.array(data[b'labels'])
            
            self.loadbatch[batch_name] = {
                'batch_name': data[b'batch_label'],
                'images': np.divide(data[b'data'], 255),
                'one_hot_labels': self.encode_label.transform(data[b'labels']),
                'labels': data[b'labels']
            }
        return self.loadbatch[batch_name]

    def get_batch(self, *args):
        bat = [self.getbat(name) for name in args]
        return {
            'batch_name': ", ".join(args),
            'images': np.vstack([b['images'] for b in bat]),
            'one_hot_labels': np.vstack([b['one_hot_labels'] for b in bat]),
            'labels': np.hstack([b['labels'] for b in bat])
        }

def disp_img(img, label='', interpolation='gaussian'):
    sqimg = np.rot90(np.reshape(img, (32, 32, 3), order='F'), k=3)
    plt.imshow(sqimg, interpolation=interpolation)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title(label)

class onelayer():
    def __init__(self, size_i, size_o, learn_rate=0.0):
        self.size_i = size_i
        self.size_o = size_o
        self.weights = np.random.normal(loc=0.0, scale=0.01, size=(size_o, size_i))
        self.bias = np.random.normal(loc=0.0, scale=0.01, size=(size_o, 1))
        self.learn_rate = learn_rate

    def softmax(self, x):
        try:
            temp = np.exp(x)
            return temp / np.sum(temp, axis=0)
        except FloatingPointError:
            return self.softmax_cbyc(x)

    def softmax_cbyc(self, x):
        cols = x.shape[1]
        result = np.finfo(float).eps * np.ones_like(x)
        for c in range(cols):
            try:
                temp = np.exp(x[:, c])
                result[:, c] = temp / np.sum(temp, axis=0)
            except FloatingPointError:
                result[np.argmax(x[:, c]), :] = 1 - np.finfo(float).eps
        return result
    
    def evaluation(self, in_data):
        X = np.reshape(in_data, (self.size_i, -1))
        class_func = self.softmax(np.dot(self.weights, X) + self.bias)
        k_max = np.argmax(class_func, axis=0)
        return class_func, k_max

    def acc(self, k_max, hot_label):
        N = k_max.shape[0]
        hot_label = np.argmax(hot_label, axis=0)
        return np.sum(k_max == hot_label) / N    

    def cost(self, class_func, hot_label):
        N = class_func.shape[1]
        class_func = np.reshape(class_func, (self.size_o, -1))
        hot_label = np.reshape(hot_label, (self.size_o, -1))

        log_arg = np.multiply(hot_label, class_func).sum(axis=0)
        log_arg[log_arg == 0] = np.finfo(float).eps

        return - np.log(log_arg).sum() / N + self.learn_rate * np.power(self.weights, 2).sum()

    def cal_gradients(self, in_data, class_func, hot_label):
        N = class_func.shape[1]

        diff_w = np.zeros_like(self.weights)
        diff_b = np.zeros_like(self.bias)

        for i in range(N):
            x = in_data[:, i]
            y = hot_label[:, i]
            p = class_func[:, i]

            t1 = np.outer(p, p)
            t2 = np.dot(y, (np.diag(p) - t1))
            t3 = np.dot(y, p)
            if t3 == 0:
                t3 = np.finfo(float).eps
            g = - t2 / t3
            
            diff_w += np.outer(g, x)
            diff_b += np.reshape(g, diff_b.shape)

        diff_w = diff_w / N + 2 * self.learn_rate * self.weights
        diff_b /= N

        return diff_w, diff_b

def finite_diff_num(in_data, hot_label, net):
    h = 1e-6  

    diff_w = np.zeros_like(net.weights)
    diff_b = np.zeros_like(net.bias)

    class_func, _ = net.evaluation(in_data)
    cost = net.cost(class_func, hot_label)

    for i in range(net.bias.shape[0]):
        net.bias[i] += h
        class_func, _ = net.evaluation(in_data)
        c2 = net.cost(class_func, hot_label)
        diff_b[i] = (c2 - cost) / h
        net.bias[i] -= h

    for i in range(net.weights.shape[0]):
        for j in range(net.weights.shape[1]):
            net.weights[i, j] += h
            class_func, _ = net.evaluation(in_data)
            c2 = net.cost(class_func, hot_label)
            diff_w[i, j] = (c2 - cost) / h
            net.weights[i, j] -= h

    return diff_w, diff_b

def out_gradient_diff(diff_w, num_w, diff_b, num_b):
    print('Gradient of weight')
    print('Difference: {:.3e}'.format(np.abs(diff_w - num_w).sum()))
    print('Mean of the values  Analytical: {:.3e}  Numerical: {:.3e}'
          .format(np.abs(diff_w).mean(), np.abs(num_w).mean()))
    print('Min of values  Analytical: {:.3e}  Numerical: {:.3e}'
          .format(np.abs(diff_w).min(),  np.abs(num_w).min()))
    print('Max of values  Analytical: {:.3e}  Numerical: {:.3e}'
          .format(np.abs(diff_w).max(),  np.abs(num_w).max()))
    print('Gradient of bias')
    print('Difference: {:.3e}'.format(np.abs(diff_b - num_b).sum()))
    print('Mean of the values  Analytical: {:.3e}  Numerical: {:.3e}'
          .format(np.abs(diff_b).mean(), np.abs(num_b).mean()))
    print('Min of values  Analytical: {:.3e}  Numerical: {:.3e}'
          .format(np.abs(diff_b).min(),  np.abs(num_b).min()))
    print('Max of values  Analytical: {:.3e}  Numerical: {:.3e}'
          .format(np.abs(diff_b).max(),  np.abs(num_b).max()))

def train(set_train, set_validate, n, 
          eta=0.01, epochs=1, 
          batch_size=None, shuffle=False, final_eta=None):
    
    t_accuracy, v_accuracy, t_cost, v_cost = [], [], [], []
    sample_total = set_train['images'].shape[0]
    batch_size = batch_size or sample_total // 100
    ind = np.arange(sample_total)
    
    for epoch_num in range(epochs):
        if shuffle:
            np.random.shuffle(ind)
        
        if final_eta:
            eta = eta - epoch_num * (eta - final_eta) / epochs
        else:
            eta = eta
        
        for start in range(0, sample_total, batch_size):
            
            batch_indexes = ind[start: start + batch_size]
            in_data = set_train['images'][batch_indexes].transpose()
            hot_label = set_train['one_hot_labels'][batch_indexes].transpose()

            class_func, k_max = n.evaluation(in_data)
            diff_w, diff_b = n.cal_gradients(in_data, class_func, hot_label)
            n.weights -= eta * diff_w
            n.bias -= eta * diff_b

        class_func, k_max = n.evaluation(set_train['images'].transpose())
        cost = n.cost(class_func, set_train['one_hot_labels'].transpose())
        acc = n.acc(k_max, set_train['one_hot_labels'].transpose())
        t_cost.append(cost)
        t_accuracy.append(acc)

        class_func, k_max = n.evaluation(set_validate['images'].transpose())
        cost = n.cost(class_func, set_validate['one_hot_labels'].transpose())
        acc = n.acc(k_max, set_validate['one_hot_labels'].transpose())
        v_cost.append(cost)
        v_accuracy.append(acc)
    return t_accuracy, v_accuracy, t_cost, v_cost

def cal_percent(n, tset, vset):
    class_func, k_max = n.evaluation(tset['images'].transpose())
    acc = n.acc(k_max, tset['one_hot_labels'].transpose())
    cost = n.cost(class_func, tset['one_hot_labels'].transpose())
    result = 'Training:\n' + \
          'Accuracy: {:.3%}\n'.format(acc) + \
          'Cost:     {:.3f}\n'.format(cost)

    class_func, k_max = n.evaluation(vset['images'].transpose())
    acc = n.acc(k_max, vset['one_hot_labels'].transpose())
    cost = n.cost(class_func, vset['one_hot_labels'].transpose())
    result += 'Validation:\n' + \
           'Accuracy: {:.3%}%\n'.format(acc) + \
           'Cost:      {:.3f}'.format(cost)
    
    return result
    
def plot_grap(t_accuracy, v_accuracy, t_cost, v_cost, destfile):
    plt.subplot(1,2,1)
    plt.plot(t_cost, 'g-', label='Training')
    plt.plot(v_cost, 'r-', label='Validation')
    plt.title('Cost Vs Epoch')
    plt.legend()
        
    plt.subplot(1,2,2)
    plt.plot(t_accuracy, 'g-', label='Training')
    plt.plot(v_accuracy, 'r-', label='Validation')
    plt.title('Accuracy Vs Epoch')
    plt.legend()
        
    plt.savefig(destfile)
    plt.clf()
    plt.close()
    return destfile

def plot_imgweight(weights, destfile, labels):
    for i, row in enumerate(weights):
        img = (row - row.min()) / (row.max() - row.min())
        plt.subplot(2, 5, i+1)
        disp_img(img, label=labels[i])
    plt.savefig(destfile)
    plt.clf()
    plt.close()
    return destfile
    
def net_train(dset, tset, vset, learn_rate, epochs, batch_size, eta, 
                     final_eta=None, shuffle=False, train_id='no_id'):
    n = onelayer(dset.size_i, dset.size_o, learn_rate=learn_rate)
    t_accuracy, v_accuracy, t_cost, v_cost = train(tset, vset, n, 
                                                     eta, epochs, batch_size, 
                                                     shuffle, final_eta)
    return {
        'model': n, 
        'validation_accuracy': v_accuracy[-1],
        'cal_percent': cal_percent(n, tset, vset),
        'weightimg': plot_imgweight(n.weights, 'weight.png'.format(train_id), dset.labels),
        'graphplot': plot_grap(t_accuracy, v_accuracy, t_cost, v_cost, 
                                                    'graph.png'.format(train_id))
    }

def report(result):
    print(result['cal_percent'])
    display(Image(result['graphplot']))
    display(Image(result['weightimg']))
    return result
